description:
&lt;p&gt;Digital Midwife advert&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Help shape the future of the digital landscape at Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and improve the care and wellbeing of women and babies in Bradford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated, enthusiastic midwife to join the Clinical Informatics team working predominately within maternity services to support the implementation of Cerner Maternity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Digital Midwife will be an effective ambassador for the trust, be credible and knowledgeable with the confidence and interpersonal skills to work with clinical, managerial and support staff at all levels across maternity services and the wider organisation. The post holder will be involved in the design, planning and implementation of Cerner Maternity and will facilitate change within Maternity Services including ensuring compliance with appropriate national and local standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will need to have IT knowledge and a skill base of both midwifery clinical practice, and the digital agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Kay Pagan, Assistant Chief Nurse for Informatics on 01274 382035 or email kay.pagan@bthft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date will be Wednesday 18 November 2020 with interviews planned for Monday 30 November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
